Elon Musk forced to step down as chairman of Tesla&#39;s board of directors
The US Securities and Exchange Commission and Tesla founder Elon Musk have settled their fraud dispute.
It is reported by CNBC News.
According to the channel, as part of the agreements reached, Musk will have to leave the post of chairman of the board of directors of Tesla.
At the same time, the commission allowed Musk to keep the post of head of Tesla.
