In addition, the company must appoint two independent directors.
Elon Musk is an American entrepreneur who is included in the list of the 50 richest people in the world according to Forbes magazine.
He is the head of the space corporation SpaceX, the neurotech company Neuralink and the developer of Tesla electric cars, as well as the co-founder of Paypal.
The US Securities and Exchange Commission has previously sued Tesla CEO Elon Musk over his tweet about a possible company buyout.
Last month, Musk announced plans to take Tesla private and buy all shares on the stock exchange at a fixed price of $420.
The share price of $420 was set allegedly &quot;due to the significance of this number in marijuana culture,&quot; Bloomberg reported earlier, citing the co-director of the commission&#39;s security department, Stephen Peikin.
At the same time, Elon Musk subsequently abandoned his plans to buy back shares.
Commenting on the lawsuit filed against him by the US Securities and Exchange Commission, the businessman said that he considers the allegations of fraud to be unfounded, and added that he was very disappointed and saddened by these claims.
&quot;Honesty is the most important value in my life, and the facts will prove that I did not violate it in any way,&quot; the businessman said in an interview with CNBC.
At the same time, in August, a group of Tesla shareholders filed a class action lawsuit against Musk, complaining about the financial losses incurred.
The plaintiffs claimed that the businessman&#39;s posts brought them losses.
In particular, one of the shareholders said that the businessman&#39;s tweets were misleading, because of which the sellers of Tesla shares were forced to buy securities at artificially high prices in order to cover their positions.
Other plaintiffs also noted that Elon Musk&#39;s careless statements led to sharp fluctuations in the course.
In September, Elon Musk was also accused of stock fraud by the head of the research company Citron Research.
Meanwhile, if Musk could not resolve his dispute with the US Securities and Exchange Commission, he would have been threatened with removal from the leadership of the company and even prison.
This, in particular, was stated to CNBC by the former chairman of the commission, Harvey Pitt.
