Today, 48 percent of Germans support Angela Merkel, which is 7 percent lower than last year.
Let&#39;s add that after the Social Democrats settled &quot;green&quot; (15%), the left (11%) and the liberals (10%).
The evolution of &quot;Alternative&quot;
The Alternative for Germany party was created in September 2012 on the basis of the Alternative Choice 2013 group, which included people from the Christian Democratic Union.
The group initially stood in opposition to the government&#39;s course, but at first it dealt only with economic issues, including the problems of the euro and interaction within the EU.
At the same time, the group opposed Germany&#39;s &quot;sponsoring&quot; of the weak EU economies, did not rule out the possibility of a return to the German mark and the country&#39;s complete withdrawal from the European Union.
As the immigration crisis deepened, the political platform of the AfD expanded.
In 2013, the group formed into a full-fledged party, which occupied the niche of Euroskeptics and began to harshly criticize the government for the failure of immigration policy.
In the last parliamentary elections in 2017, the AfD managed to get into the Bundestag for the first time, winning 94 seats (out of 709).
