These words have really frightening &quot;relatives&quot;: daos - &quot;wolf&quot; (crushing sheep), deyja - &quot;to die&quot; and dvaidī - &quot;oppress&quot;.
The similar phonetic appearance of the words &quot;pressure&quot; and &quot;pressure&quot;, as well as the inevitable obsolescence of the latter, forced them to enter into contamination.
